{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"My topic"},{"time":2000,"text":"is economic growth in China and India."},{"time":5000,"text":"And the question I want to explore with you"},{"time":8000,"text":"is whether or not"},{"time":10000,"text":"democracy has helped or has hindered"},{"time":13000,"text":"economic growth."},{"time":15000,"text":"You may say this is not fair,"},{"time":17000,"text":"because I'm selecting two countries"},{"time":20000,"text":"to make a case against democracy."},{"time":23000,"text":"Actually, exactly the opposite"},{"time":26000,"text":"is what I'm going to do."},{"time":28000,"text":"I'm going to use these two countries"},{"time":30000,"text":"to make an economic argument for democracy,"},{"time":33000,"text":"rather than against democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36000,"text":"The first question there"},{"time":38000,"text":"is why China has grown so much faster"},{"time":40000,"text":"than India."},{"time":42000,"text":"Over the last 30 years,"},{"time":44000,"text":"in terms of the GDP growth rates,"},{"time":47000,"text":"China has grown at twice the rate of India."},{"time":51000,"text":"In the last five years,"},{"time":53000,"text":"the two countries have begun to converge somewhat"},{"time":56000,"text":"in economic growth."},{"time":58000,"text":"But over the last 30 years,"},{"time":60000,"text":"China undoubtedly"},{"time":62000,"text":"has done much better than India."},{"time":65000,"text":"One simple answer"},{"time":67000,"text":"is China has Shanghai and India has Mumbai."},{"time":70000,"text":"Look at the skyline of Shanghai."},{"time":73000,"text":"This is the Pudong area."},{"time":75000,"text":"The picture on India"},{"time":77000,"text":"is the Dharavi slum of Mumbai"},{"time":79000,"text":"in India."},{"time":81000,"text":"The idea there"},{"time":83000,"text":"behind these two pictures"},{"time":85000,"text":"is that the Chinese government"},{"time":87000,"text":"can act above rule of law."},{"time":89000,"text":"It can plan"},{"time":91000,"text":"for the long-term benefits of the country"},{"time":93000,"text":"and in the process,"},{"time":95000,"text":"evict millions of people --"},{"time":97000,"text":"that's just a small technical issue."},{"time":100000,"text":"Whereas in India, you cannot do that,"},{"time":102000,"text":"because you have to listen to the public."},{"time":105000,"text":"You're being constrained by the public's opinion."},{"time":107000,"text":"Even Prime Minister Manmohan Singh"},{"time":110000,"text":"agrees with that view."},{"time":112000,"text":"In an interview"},{"time":114000,"text":"printed in the financial press of India,"},{"time":116000,"text":"He said that he wants to make Mumbai"},{"time":119000,"text":"another Shanghai."},{"time":121000,"text":"This is an Oxford-trained economist"},{"time":124000,"text":"steeped in humanistic values,"},{"time":128000,"text":"and yet he agrees"},{"time":130000,"text":"with the high-pressure tactics of Shanghai."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134000,"text":"So let me call it the Shanghai model of economic growth,"},{"time":137000,"text":"that emphasizes the following features"},{"time":141000,"text":"for promoting economic development:"},{"time":143000,"text":"infrastructures, airports,"},{"time":145000,"text":"highways, bridges, things like that."},{"time":148000,"text":"And you need a strong government to do that,"},{"time":151000,"text":"because you cannot respect private property rights."},{"time":154000,"text":"You cannot be constrained by the public's opinion."},{"time":157000,"text":"You need also state ownership,"},{"time":159000,"text":"especially of land assets,"},{"time":162000,"text":"in order to build and roll out infrastructures"},{"time":165000,"text":"very quickly."},{"time":167000,"text":"The implication of that model"},{"time":169000,"text":"is that democracy"},{"time":171000,"text":"is a hindrance for economic growth,"},{"time":173000,"text":"rather than a facilitator of economic growth."},{"time":177000,"text":"Here's the key question."},{"time":179000,"text":"Just how important are infrastructures"},{"time":182000,"text":"for economic growth?"},{"time":184000,"text":"This is a key issue."},{"time":186000,"text":"If you believe that infrastructures are very important for economic growth,"},{"time":190000,"text":"then you would argue a strong government is necessary"},{"time":193000,"text":"to promote growth."},{"time":195000,"text":"If you believe"},{"time":197000,"text":"that infrastructures are not as important as many people believe,"},{"time":200000,"text":"then you will put less emphasis"},{"time":202000,"text":"on strong government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"So to illustrate that question,"},{"time":206000,"text":"let me give you two countries."},{"time":208000,"text":"And for the sake of brevity,"},{"time":210000,"text":"I'll call one country Country 1"},{"time":212000,"text":"and the other country Country 2."},{"time":214000,"text":"Country 1"},{"time":216000,"text":"has a systematic advantage over Country 2"},{"time":219000,"text":"in infrastructures."},{"time":221000,"text":"Country 1 has more telephones,"},{"time":224000,"text":"and Country 1 has a longer system of railways."},{"time":227000,"text":"So if I were to ask you,"},{"time":230000,"text":"\"Which is China"},{"time":232000,"text":"and which is India,"},{"time":234000,"text":"and which country has grown faster?\""},{"time":236000,"text":"if you believe in the infrastructure view,"},{"time":239000,"text":"then you will say, \"Country 1 must be China."},{"time":242000,"text":"They must have done better, in terms of economic growth."},{"time":244000,"text":"And Country 2 is possibly India.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"Actually the country with more telephones"},{"time":251000,"text":"is the Soviet Union,"},{"time":253000,"text":"and the data referred to 1989."},{"time":256000,"text":"After the country reported very impressive statistics on telephones,"},{"time":261000,"text":"the country collapsed."},{"time":264000,"text":"That's not too good."},{"time":266000,"text":"The picture there is Khrushchev."},{"time":268000,"text":"I know that in 1989"},{"time":270000,"text":"he no longer ruled the Soviet Union,"},{"time":272000,"text":"but that's the best picture that I can find."},{"time":275000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":277000,"text":"Telephones, infrastructures"},{"time":279000,"text":"do not guarantee you economic growth."},{"time":281000,"text":"Country 2, that has fewer telephones,"},{"time":284000,"text":"is China."},{"time":286000,"text":"Since 1989,"},{"time":288000,"text":"the country has performed at a double-digit rate"},{"time":290000,"text":"every year for the last 20 years."},{"time":293000,"text":"If you know nothing about China and the Soviet Union"},{"time":296000,"text":"other than the fact about their telephones,"},{"time":299000,"text":"you would have made a poor prediction"},{"time":301000,"text":"about their economic growth"},{"time":303000,"text":"in the next two decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305000,"text":"Country 1, that has a longer system of railways,"},{"time":308000,"text":"is actually India."},{"time":310000,"text":"And Country 2 is China."},{"time":313000,"text":"This is a very little known fact"},{"time":316000,"text":"about the two countries."},{"time":318000,"text":"Yes, today China has a huge infrastructure advantage"},{"time":320000,"text":"over India."},{"time":322000,"text":"But for many years,"},{"time":324000,"text":"until the late 1990s,"},{"time":326000,"text":"China had an infrastructure disadvantage"},{"time":328000,"text":"vis-a-vis India."},{"time":330000,"text":"In developing countries,"},{"time":332000,"text":"the most common mode of transportation"},{"time":335000,"text":"is the railways,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and the British built a lot of railways in India."},{"time":340000,"text":"India is the smaller of the two countries,"},{"time":343000,"text":"and yet it had a longer system of railways"},{"time":346000,"text":"until the late 1990s."},{"time":348000,"text":"So clearly,"},{"time":350000,"text":"infrastructure doesn't explain"},{"time":352000,"text":"why China did better before the late 1990s,"},{"time":355000,"text":"as compared with India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":357000,"text":"In fact, if you look at the evidence worldwide,"},{"time":361000,"text":"the evidence is more supportive of the view"},{"time":364000,"text":"that the infrastructure are actually the result of economic growth."},{"time":368000,"text":"The economy grows,"},{"time":370000,"text":"government accumulates more resources,"},{"time":372000,"text":"and the government can invest in infrastructure --"},{"time":375000,"text":"rather than infrastructure being a cause"},{"time":378000,"text":"for economic growth."},{"time":380000,"text":"And this is clearly the story"},{"time":382000,"text":"of the Chinese economic growth."},{"time":385000,"text":"Let me look at this question more directly."},{"time":387000,"text":"Is democracy bad for economic growth?"},{"time":390000,"text":"Now let's turn to two countries,"},{"time":392000,"text":"Country A and Country B."},{"time":395000,"text":"Country A, in 1990,"},{"time":397000,"text":"had about $300 per capita GDP"},{"time":400000,"text":"as compared with Country B,"},{"time":402000,"text":"which had $460 in per capita GDP."},{"time":405000,"text":"By 2008,"},{"time":407000,"text":"Country A has surpassed Country B"},{"time":410000,"text":"with $700 per capita GDP"},{"time":413000,"text":"as compared with $650 per capita GDP."},{"time":417000,"text":"Both countries are in Asia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"If I were to ask you,"},{"time":421000,"text":"\"Which are the two Asian countries?"},{"time":423000,"text":"And which one is a democracy?\""},{"time":425000,"text":"you may argue,"},{"time":427000,"text":"\"Well, maybe Country A is China"},{"time":429000,"text":"and Country B is India.\""},{"time":431000,"text":"In fact, Country A"},{"time":433000,"text":"is democratic India,"},{"time":435000,"text":"and Country B is Pakistan --"},{"time":438000,"text":"the country that has a long period"},{"time":440000,"text":"of military rule."},{"time":442000,"text":"And it's very common"},{"time":444000,"text":"that we compare India with China."},{"time":448000,"text":"That's because the two countries"},{"time":450000,"text":"have about the same population size."},{"time":453000,"text":"But the more natural comparison"},{"time":455000,"text":"is actually between India and Pakistan."},{"time":457000,"text":"Those two countries are geographically similar."},{"time":460000,"text":"They have a complicated, but shared common history."},{"time":464000,"text":"By that comparison,"},{"time":466000,"text":"democracy looks very, very good"},{"time":468000,"text":"in terms of economic growth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471000,"text":"So why do economists fall in love"},{"time":474000,"text":"with authoritarian governments?"},{"time":477000,"text":"One reason is the East Asian Model."},{"time":479000,"text":"In East Asia,"},{"time":481000,"text":"we have had successful economic growth stories"},{"time":484000,"text":"such as Korea, Taiwan,"},{"time":486000,"text":"Hong Kong and Singapore."},{"time":488000,"text":"Some of these economies"},{"time":490000,"text":"were ruled by authoritarian governments"},{"time":492000,"text":"in the 60s and 70s"},{"time":494000,"text":"and 1980s."},{"time":496000,"text":"The problem with that view"},{"time":498000,"text":"is like asking all the winners of lotteries,"},{"time":501000,"text":"\"Have you won the lottery?\""},{"time":504000,"text":"And they all tell you, \"Yes, we have won the lottery.\""},{"time":506000,"text":"And then you draw the conclusion"},{"time":508000,"text":"the odds of winning the lottery"},{"time":511000,"text":"are 100 percent."},{"time":513000,"text":"The reason is you never go"},{"time":515000,"text":"and bother to ask the losers"},{"time":517000,"text":"who also purchased lottery tickets"},{"time":519000,"text":"and didn't end up winning the prize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523000,"text":"For each of these successful authoritarian governments"},{"time":526000,"text":"in East Asia,"},{"time":528000,"text":"there's a matched failure."},{"time":531000,"text":"Korea succeeded, North Korea didn't."},{"time":534000,"text":"Taiwan succeeded, China under Mao Zedong didn't."},{"time":537000,"text":"Burma didn't succeed."},{"time":539000,"text":"The Philippines didn't succeed."},{"time":541000,"text":"If you look at the statistical evidence worldwide,"},{"time":544000,"text":"there's really no support for the idea"},{"time":547000,"text":"that authoritarian governments"},{"time":549000,"text":"hold a systematic edge over democracies"},{"time":552000,"text":"in terms of economic growth."},{"time":554000,"text":"So the East Asian model"},{"time":556000,"text":"has this massive selection bias --"},{"time":558000,"text":"it is known as selecting on a dependent variable,"},{"time":561000,"text":"something we always tell our students to avoid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565000,"text":"So exactly why did China grow so much faster?"},{"time":570000,"text":"I will take you to the Cultural Revolution,"},{"time":572000,"text":"when China went mad,"},{"time":574000,"text":"and compare that country's performance with India"},{"time":577000,"text":"under Indira Gandhi."},{"time":579000,"text":"The question there is: Which country did better,"},{"time":582000,"text":"China or India?"},{"time":584000,"text":"China was during the Cultural Revolution."},{"time":586000,"text":"It turns out even during the Cultural Revolution,"},{"time":588000,"text":"China out-perfomed India"},{"time":590000,"text":"in terms of GDP growth"},{"time":592000,"text":"by an average of about 2.2 percent every year"},{"time":595000,"text":"in terms of per capita GDP."},{"time":598000,"text":"So that's when China was mad."},{"time":600000,"text":"The whole country went mad."},{"time":603000,"text":"It must mean that the country"},{"time":605000,"text":"had something so advantageous to itself in terms of economic growth"},{"time":609000,"text":"to overcome the negative effects"},{"time":612000,"text":"of the Cultural Revolution."},{"time":614000,"text":"The advantage the country had"},{"time":616000,"text":"was human capital --"},{"time":619000,"text":"nothing else but human capital."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621000,"text":"This is the world development index indicator data"},{"time":625000,"text":"in the early 1990s."},{"time":627000,"text":"And this is the earliest data that I can find."},{"time":630000,"text":"The adult literacy rate in China"},{"time":633000,"text":"is 77 percent"},{"time":635000,"text":"as compared with 48 percent in India."},{"time":638000,"text":"The contrast in literacy rates"},{"time":641000,"text":"is especially sharp"},{"time":643000,"text":"between Chinese women and Indian women."},{"time":646000,"text":"I haven't told you about the definition of literacy."},{"time":650000,"text":"In China, the definition of literacy"},{"time":653000,"text":"is the ability to read and write"},{"time":655000,"text":"1,500 Chinese characters."},{"time":658000,"text":"In India, the definition of literacy,"},{"time":661000,"text":"operating definition of literacy,"},{"time":663000,"text":"is the ability, the grand ability,"},{"time":666000,"text":"to write your own name"},{"time":668000,"text":"in whatever language you happen to speak."},{"time":672000,"text":"The gap between the two countries in terms of literacy"},{"time":674000,"text":"is much more substantial"},{"time":676000,"text":"than the data here indicated."},{"time":679000,"text":"If you go to other sources of data"},{"time":681000,"text":"such as Human Development Index,"},{"time":683000,"text":"that data series,"},{"time":685000,"text":"go back to the early 1970s,"},{"time":688000,"text":"you see exactly the same contrast."},{"time":690000,"text":"China held a huge advantage"},{"time":692000,"text":"in terms of human capital"},{"time":694000,"text":"vis-a-vis India."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696000,"text":"Life expectancies:"},{"time":698000,"text":"as early as 1965,"},{"time":700000,"text":"China had a huge advantage in life expectancy."},{"time":704000,"text":"On average, as a Chinese in 1965,"},{"time":707000,"text":"you lived 10 years more"},{"time":709000,"text":"than an average Indian."},{"time":711000,"text":"So if you have a choice"},{"time":713000,"text":"between being a Chinese and being an Indian,"},{"time":715000,"text":"you would want to become a Chinese"},{"time":717000,"text":"in order to live 10 years longer."},{"time":720000,"text":"If you made that decision in 1965,"},{"time":722000,"text":"the down side of that"},{"time":724000,"text":"is the next year we have the Cultural Revolution."},{"time":726000,"text":"So you have to always think carefully"},{"time":729000,"text":"about these decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731000,"text":"If you cannot chose your nationality,"},{"time":734000,"text":"then you will want to become an Indian man."},{"time":737000,"text":"Because, as an Indian man,"},{"time":739000,"text":"you have about two years of life expectancy advantage"},{"time":742000,"text":"vis-a-vis Indian women."},{"time":745000,"text":"This is an extremely strange fact."},{"time":748000,"text":"It's very rare among countries"},{"time":751000,"text":"to have this kind of pattern."},{"time":753000,"text":"It shows the systematic discrimination and biases"},{"time":756000,"text":"in the Indian society"},{"time":758000,"text":"against women."},{"time":760000,"text":"The good news is, by 2006,"},{"time":762000,"text":"India has closed the gap"},{"time":764000,"text":"between men and women"},{"time":766000,"text":"in terms of life expectancy."},{"time":769000,"text":"Today, Indian women have a sizable life expectancy edge"},{"time":772000,"text":"over Indian men."},{"time":774000,"text":"So India is reverting to the normal."},{"time":777000,"text":"But India still has a lot of work to do"},{"time":779000,"text":"in terms of gender equality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781000,"text":"These are the two pictures"},{"time":783000,"text":"taken of garment factories in Guangdong Province"},{"time":786000,"text":"and garment factories in India."},{"time":789000,"text":"In China, it's all women."},{"time":791000,"text":"60 to 80 percent of the workforce in China is women"},{"time":794000,"text":"in the coastal part of the country,"},{"time":796000,"text":"whereas in India, it's all men."},{"time":799000,"text":"Financial Times printed this picture"},{"time":801000,"text":"of an Indian textile factory"},{"time":803000,"text":"with the title, \"India Poised to Overtake China in Textile.\""},{"time":807000,"text":"By looking at these two pictures,"},{"time":809000,"text":"I say no, it won't overtake China for a while."},{"time":813000,"text":"If you look at other East Asian countries,"},{"time":815000,"text":"women there play a hugely important role"},{"time":819000,"text":"in terms of economic take-off --"},{"time":821000,"text":"in terms of creating the manufacturing miracle"},{"time":824000,"text":"associated with East Asia."},{"time":826000,"text":"India still has a long way to go"},{"time":828000,"text":"to catch up with China."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830000,"text":"Then the issue is,"},{"time":832000,"text":"what about the Chinese political system?"},{"time":834000,"text":"You talk about human capital,"},{"time":836000,"text":"you talk about education and public health."},{"time":838000,"text":"What about the political system?"},{"time":840000,"text":"Isn't it true that the one-party political system"},{"time":843000,"text":"has facilitated economic growth in China?"},{"time":847000,"text":"Actually, the answer is more nuanced and subtle than that."},{"time":851000,"text":"It depends on a distinction that you draw"},{"time":854000,"text":"between statics of the political system"},{"time":857000,"text":"and the dynamics of the political system."},{"time":859000,"text":"Statically, China is a one-party system,"},{"time":862000,"text":"authoritarian -- there's no question about it."},{"time":865000,"text":"Dynamically, it has changed over time"},{"time":868000,"text":"to become less authoritarian and more democratic."},{"time":871000,"text":"When you explain change --"},{"time":873000,"text":"for example, economic growth;"},{"time":875000,"text":"economic growth is about change --"},{"time":877000,"text":"when you explain change,"},{"time":879000,"text":"you use other things that have changed to explain change,"},{"time":882000,"text":"rather than using the constant to explain change."},{"time":886000,"text":"Sometimes a fixed effect can explain change,"},{"time":889000,"text":"but a fixed effect only explains changes"},{"time":892000,"text":"in interaction with the things that change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":895000,"text":"In terms of the political changes,"},{"time":897000,"text":"they have introduced village elections."},{"time":899000,"text":"They have increased the security of proprietors."},{"time":903000,"text":"And they have increased the security"},{"time":906000,"text":"with long-term land leases."},{"time":908000,"text":"There are also financial reforms in rural China."},{"time":911000,"text":"There is also a rural entrepreneurial revolution in China."},{"time":914000,"text":"To me, the pace of political changes"},{"time":917000,"text":"is too slow, too gradual."},{"time":919000,"text":"And my own view is the country"},{"time":921000,"text":"is going to face some substantial challenges,"},{"time":923000,"text":"because they have not moved further and faster on political reforms."},{"time":927000,"text":"But nevertheless,"},{"time":929000,"text":"the system has moved in a more liberal direction,"},{"time":932000,"text":"moved in a more democratic direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":936000,"text":"You can apply exactly the same dynamic perspective on India."},{"time":940000,"text":"In fact, when India was growing"},{"time":942000,"text":"at a Hindu rate of growth --"},{"time":944000,"text":"about one percent, two percent a year --"},{"time":946000,"text":"that was when India was least democratic."},{"time":949000,"text":"Indira Gandhi declared emergency rule in 1975."},{"time":953000,"text":"The Indian government owned and operated"},{"time":956000,"text":"all the TV stations."},{"time":958000,"text":"A little-known fact about India in the 1990s"},{"time":961000,"text":"is that the country"},{"time":963000,"text":"not only has undertaken economic reforms,"},{"time":966000,"text":"the country has also undertaken political reforms"},{"time":969000,"text":"by introducing village self-rule,"},{"time":972000,"text":"privatization of media"},{"time":975000,"text":"and introducing freedom of information acts."},{"time":979000,"text":"So the dynamic perspective"},{"time":981000,"text":"fits both with China and in India"},{"time":983000,"text":"in terms of the direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985000,"text":"Why do many people believe"},{"time":988000,"text":"that India is still a growth disaster?"},{"time":991000,"text":"One reason"},{"time":993000,"text":"is they are always comparing India with China."},{"time":996000,"text":"But China is a superstar"},{"time":998000,"text":"in terms of economic growth."},{"time":1000000,"text":"If you are a NBA player"},{"time":1002000,"text":"and you are always being compared to Michael Jordan,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"you're going to look not so impressive."},{"time":1007000,"text":"But that doesn't mean"},{"time":1009000,"text":"that you're a bad basketball player."},{"time":1011000,"text":"Comparing with a superstar"},{"time":1013000,"text":"is the wrong benchmark."},{"time":1015000,"text":"In fact, if you compare India"},{"time":1017000,"text":"with the average developing country,"},{"time":1019000,"text":"even before the more recent period"},{"time":1022000,"text":"of acceleration of Indian growth --"},{"time":1024000,"text":"now India is growing between eight and nine percent --"},{"time":1027000,"text":"even before this period,"},{"time":1029000,"text":"India was ranked fourth in terms of economic growth"},{"time":1032000,"text":"among emerging economies."},{"time":1035000,"text":"This is a very impressive record indeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039000,"text":"Let's think about the future:"},{"time":1041000,"text":"the dragon vis-a-vis the elephant."},{"time":1044000,"text":"Which country has the growth momentum?"},{"time":1047000,"text":"China, I believe, still has"},{"time":1050000,"text":"some of the excellent raw fundamentals --"},{"time":1053000,"text":"mostly the social capital,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"the public health,"},{"time":1057000,"text":"the sense of egalitarianism"},{"time":1059000,"text":"that you don't find in India."},{"time":1061000,"text":"But I believe that India has the momentum."},{"time":1063000,"text":"It has the improving fundamentals."},{"time":1065000,"text":"The government has invested in basic education,"},{"time":1068000,"text":"has invested in basic health."},{"time":1070000,"text":"I believe the government should do more,"},{"time":1072000,"text":"but nevertheless, the direction it is moving in"},{"time":1074000,"text":"is the right direction."},{"time":1076000,"text":"India has the right institutional conditions"},{"time":1079000,"text":"for economic growth,"},{"time":1081000,"text":"whereas China is still struggling"},{"time":1083000,"text":"with political reforms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085000,"text":"I believe that the political reforms are a must for China"},{"time":1088000,"text":"to maintain its growth."},{"time":1091000,"text":"And it's very important to have political reforms,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"to have widely shared benefits of economic growth."},{"time":1096000,"text":"I don't know whether that's going to happen or not,"},{"time":1098000,"text":"but I'm an optimist."},{"time":1100000,"text":"Hopefully, five years from now, I'm going to report to TEDGlobal"},{"time":1103000,"text":"that political reforms will happen in China."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1105000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1107000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}